FBIS4-15655 "drsov069_b_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Grenade Incident at Moscow Subway Station; 13 Hurt Grenade Incident at Moscow Subway Station; 13 Hurt LD1004120394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1149 GMT 10 Apr 94 LD1004120394 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] [Text] Moscow April 10 TASS -- Thirteen people, four of them chance passers-by, were injured in a grenade blast near Profsoyuznaya metro station at 22.20 here on Saturday. Nine people were hospitalised. An F-1 grenade was hurled from a dark-coloured Mercedes car without plate numbers in the direction of a group of Caucasians who stood near kiosks run by the Raketa Limited Partnership, a spokesman in Moscow's South Western District prefecture, told ITAR-TASS.
